	     <form action=/cgi-bin/mrate.pl name=f104335287886135>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=>RE: Never Satisfied</a> <a id=fs8 href=#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Thu, Jan 23rd 3:43 PM 2003</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=120740><span id=Scholar>ayere</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>27 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [2.98]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Well, first off Queball is heading in the right direction. But I'll add this: you don't get a sense of a character class/race until it gets to at least the early to mid 30's. Every class (caster, melee, hybrid) is very similar in the low teens with very little interesting stuff to do. For example, some clerics and wizards are still melee'ing into their late teens (lol saw one Battle Cleric in her late 20's and laughed my butt off).&nbsp;&nbsp;<br><br>For an SK or Ranger, they don't come into their own until at least the 30's - Ranger's maybe mid 50's with some AA's :) . <br><br>Dyre  - 53 SK<br>Syre  - 55 Necro (new Main)<br>Ayere - 49 Ranger (semi-retired)<br>44 Druid, 39 Bard, 49 Monk, 48 Rogue, 44 Enchanter - all deleted, no offense to anyone - they were fun, but I needed to concentrate<br><br>Oh, and Druids are very versatile, but for truely awesome power, try a Necro. :)  SK's derive for Necro's - so there you go. Also, the 50's for SK's are interesting again now that PoP has come out. If you like tanking, pulling, and being the center of attention of the group and still want the option/power to play Solo occasionally, go SK. If you like being the center of the cleric's attention, go Ranger and get 2 lammys :)  Had my Ranger set up this way and I got kicked out of a few groups. The epic sounds sick - slow/haste *and* the ability to track? OMG! Hmmm... maybe Ayere needs to come out of retirement. ;)<br><br>Anyway, pick one character that suits your personality - sounds like SK may be a good fit for you - and play it into the 30's and then decide.<br><br>peAce<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Thu Jan 23 15:23:32 2003</em></p>&nbsp;<br></td></td></tr>
